@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<hgroup class="title">
    <h1>@ViewBag.Title </h1>
    <h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
</hgroup>

<article>
    <p>
	    The "Reader Book Notes" program was designed to provide readers with a place to read about other readers comments 
		about a particular book.
    </p>

    <p>
	    The program also allows you to add your own comments to notes that already exist for a book.  If you don't find 
	    the book, You can add the book and include your own notes.  When you are adding a new book, please include Title, 
		Author, publisher, and ISBN number (usually located in the first four or five pages added by the publisher).
    </p>

    <p>
	    If you decide to add your own notes, you must create an account.  This account will only be used to identify the added notes. 
		The account will also be used to track the reader ratings as they are added to each note.
    </p>
</article>
